1/29

(Playlist 12)

Catholic mass
  A reenactment of the sacrifice of Christ
  Most solemn ritual of the Catholic Church
  Collection of prayers that makes up the mass = the liturgy

Catholic liturgy
  Ordinary: texts that remain the same in every Mass
  Proper: texts that vary from day to day throughout the church year

Organum: a musical elaboration of planchant
  Def: a type of medieval homophony or polyphony with one sustained part of note and other movable parts

The reformation: three streams
  Growing sense that the church elite
  Middle class, educated Euros wanted to manage their own spiritual life more than Church
  Kings and Princes resented the Church's control over hand, property and wealth.

Three protestant reformation
  Lutheran
    Church corruption / hierachy. Papal authority.
	Purgatory & indulgences
	Separation of Church & State
	Sacraments (how many & the nature of the host)
	Language of Bible, music
  Calvin
    Agrees with Luther on: Church corruption, purgatory, language, no transubstantiation.
	Disgree: means of salvation (predestination), church & state (christianize the government)
  Anglican

Council of trent


